enhanced_by.reason: Both methods modify the internal state of the queue by adding or removing elements.
The clear method resets the queue state, which can be useful for setting up a test scenario before invoking remove.
The peek method returns the head of the queue without removing it, which can be used to verify the state of the queue before and after the remove operation.
The size method can be used to verify the number of elements in the queue before and after the remove operation.
